HEADWORD: fiddleneck
<hw>fiddleneck</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>hairy annual plant (<spn>Phacelia
tanacetifolia</spn>) of California to Mexico with crowded cymes of small
blue to lilac or mauve flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> <spn>Phacelia tanacetifolia</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>fiddle-shaped</ent>⟦br⟧
